OL,6,FThe Northern Lights are a result of
OL,7,Fsolar storms that cause the sun to
OL,8,Fthrow out huge bursts of energy and
OL,9,Fplasma, these then react with gases in
OL,10,Fthe Earth's atmosphere to create
OL,11,Fgreens (Oxygen) as well as pinks,
OL,12,Fblues and purples (Nitrogen).
OL,14,FThe Perseid meteor shower is created
OL,15,Fby dusty debris left by Comet Swift-
OL,16,FTuttle which orbits the Sun once every
OL,17,F133 years.
